{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- Add categories where indicated at the bottom of this page and interwikis at Wikidata -->
== Usage ==
This is a [[WP:WRAPPER|wrapper]] for {{tl|If IP}} intended for processes that a user must be logged in to complete. It outputs nothing if viewed by a logged in user but a message to log in or create an account when viewed logged out. The links are structured such that the user will automatically return to the page once they're logged in.

==Parameters==
<templatedata>
{
	"params": {
		"1": {
			"description": "The content shown only if logged in. Cannot handle normal line breaks; use {{parabr}} instead.",
			"type": "content",
			"suggested": true
		},
		"return": {
			"description": "The page to automatically return to after the user completes  registration. Must be URL encoded, which can be done via Name+of+the+page.",
			"example": "Template+talk%3ADid+you+know%23Instructions+for+nominators",
			"type": "string",
			"autovalue": "Template:Must_log_in/doc",
			"suggested": true
		},
		"extra": {
			"description": "Additional instructions for logged out users. Cannot handle normal line breaks; use {{parabr}} instead.",
			"type": "content"
		}
	}
}
</templatedata>

<includeonly>{{sandbox other||
<!-- Categories below this line; interwikis at Wikidata -->
[[Category:Wikipedia formatting templates]]
}}</includeonly>

